c.name: MSK_SOLVE_DUAL

sec.cmnt: The enumeration type containing all string parameters.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_DATA_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: Data are read and written to this file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_PARAM_READ_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: Modifications to the parameter database is read from this file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_PARAM_WRITE_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: The parameter database is written to this file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_PARAM_COMMENT_SIGN
p.cmnt: Only the first character in this string is used. It is considered as a start of comment sign in the |mosek| parameter file. Spaces are ignored in the string.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_DEBUG_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: |mosek| debug file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_BAS_SOL_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the ``bas`` solution file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_ITR_SOL_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the ``itr`` solution file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_INT_SOL_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the ``int`` solution file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_SOL_FILTER_XC_LOW
p.cmnt: A filter used to determine which constraints should be listed in the solution file. A value of :math:`0.5` means that all constraints having ``xc[i]>0.5`` should be listed, whereas ``+0.5`` means that all constraints having ``xc[i]>=blc[i]+0.5`` should be listed. An empty filter means that no filter is applied.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_SOL_FILTER_XC_UPR
p.cmnt: A filter used to determine which constraints should be listed in the solution file. A value of ``0.5`` means that all constraints having ``xc[i]<0.5`` should be listed, whereas ``-0.5`` means all constraints having ``xc[i]<=buc[i]-0.5`` should be listed. An empty filter means that no filter is applied.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_SOL_FILTER_XX_LOW
p.cmnt: A filter used to determine which variables should be listed in the solution file. A value of "0.5" means that all constraints having ``xx[j]>=0.5`` should be listed, whereas "+0.5" means that all constraints having ``xx[j]>=blx[j]+0.5`` should be listed. An empty filter means no filter is applied.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_SOL_FILTER_XX_UPR
p.cmnt: A filter used to determine which variables should be listed in the solution file. A value of "0.5" means that all constraints having ``xx[j]<0.5`` should be printed, whereas "-0.5" means all constraints having ``xx[j]<=bux[j]-0.5`` should be listed. An empty filter means no filter is applied.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_READ_MPS_OBJ_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the free constraint used as objective function. An empty name means that the first constraint is used as objective function.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_READ_MPS_RAN_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the RANGE vector used. An empty name means that the first RANGE vector is used.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_READ_MPS_RHS_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the RHS used. An empty name means that the first RHS vector is used.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_READ_MPS_BOU_NAME
p.cmnt: Name of the BOUNDS vector used. An empty name means that the first BOUNDS vector is used.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_STAT_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt: Statistics file name.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_STAT_NAME
p.cmnt: Name used when writing the statistics file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_STAT_KEY
p.cmnt: Key used when writing the summary file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_WRITE_LP_GEN_VAR_NAME
p.cmnt: Sometimes when an LP file is written additional variables must be inserted. They will have the prefix denoted by this parameter.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_SENSITIVITY_RES_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt:
.. msk_only:: cmdtools
Not applicable.
.. msk_only:: optimizer
If this is a nonempty string, then :msk:func:`task.sensitivityreport` writes results to this file.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_SENSITIVITY_FILE_NAME
p.cmnt:
.. msk_only:: cmdtools
Not applicable.
.. msk_only:: optimizer
If defined :msk:func:`task.sensitivityreport` reads this file as a sensitivity analysis data file specifying the type of analysis to be done.
.. msk_only:: (not optimizer) and (not cmdtools)
If defined, |mosek| reads this file as a sensitivity analysis data file specifying the type of analysis to be done.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_MIO_DEBUG_STRING
p.cmnt: For internal debugging purposes.

p.name: MSK_SPAR_REMOTE_ACCESS_TOKEN
p.cmnt: An access token used to submit tasks to a remote |mosek| server. An access token is a random 32-byte string encoded in base64, i.e. it is a 44 character ASCII string.

sec.cmnt: The enumeration type containing all integer parameters.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_AUTO_UPDATE_SOL_INFO
p.cmnt: Controls whether the solution information items are automatically updated after an optimization is performed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_REMOVE_UNUSED_SOLUTIONS
p.cmnt: Removes unsued solutions before the optimization is performed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_HOTSTART
p.cmnt: Currently not in use.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_MT_USER_CB
p.cmnt: If true user callbacks are called from each thread used by mixed-integer optimizer. Otherwise it is only called from a single thread.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_NUM_THREADS
p.cmnt: Controls the number of threads employed by the optimizer. If set to 0 the number of threads used will be equal to the number of cores detected on the machine.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_MULTI_THREAD
p.cmnt: Controls whether the interior-point optimizers are allowed to employ multiple threads if more threads is available.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_TIMING_LEVEL
p.cmnt: Controls the amount of timing performed inside |mosek|.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MT_SPINCOUNT
p.cmnt: Set the number of iterations to spin before sleeping.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MAX_NUM_WARNINGS
p.cmnt: Each warning is shown a limit number times controlled by this parameter. A negative value is identical to infinite number of times.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: The parameter controls which optimizer is used to optimize the task.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_BI_MAX_ITERATIONS
p.cmnt: Controls the maximum number of simplex iterations allowed to optimize a basis after the basis identification.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LICENSE_TRH_EXPIRY_WRN
p.cmnt: If a license feature expires in a numbers days less than the value of this parameter then a warning will be issued.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_CUT_SECOND_OPT
p.cmnt: If a task is employed to solve a sequence of optimization problems, then the value of the log levels is reduced by the value of this parameter. E.g :msk:iparam:`log` and :msk:iparam:`log_sim` are reduced by the value of this parameter for the second and any subsequent optimizations.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_ANA_PRO
p.cmnt: Controls amount of output from the problem analyzer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_RESPONSE
p.cmnt: Controls amount of output printed when response codes are reported. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_BI
p.cmnt: Controls the amount of output printed by the basis identification procedure. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_BI_FREQ
p.cmnt: Controls how frequent the optimizer outputs information about the basis identification and how frequent the user-defined callback function is called.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_BI_CLEAN_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: Controls which simplex optimizer is used in the clean-up phase.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_MAX_NUM_REFINEMENT_STEPS
p.cmnt: Maximum number of steps to be used by the iterative refinement of the search direction. A negative value implies that the optimizer chooses the maximum number of iterative refinement steps.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_STARTING_POINT
p.cmnt: Starting point used by the interior-point optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_DIFF_STEP
p.cmnt: Controls whether different step sizes are allowed in the primal and dual space.

values_from.ref: Different step sizes are allowed.
Different step sizes are not allowed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_SCALING
p.cmnt: Controls how the problem is scaled before the interior-point optimizer is used.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_SOLVE_FORM
p.cmnt: Controls whether the primal or the dual problem is solved.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_INTPNT
p.cmnt: Controls amount of output printed by the interior-point optimizer. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_MAX_ITERATIONS
p.cmnt: Controls the maximum number of iterations allowed in the interior-point optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_ORDER_METHOD
p.cmnt: Controls the ordering strategy used by the interior-point optimizer when factorizing the Newton equation system.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_BASIS
p.cmnt: Controls whether the interior-point optimizer also computes an optimal basis.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_BI_IGNORE_MAX_ITER
p.cmnt: If the parameter :msk:iparam:`intpnt_basis` has the value :msk:const:`basindtype.no_error` and the interior-point optimizer has terminated due to maximum number of iterations, then basis identification is performed if this parameter has the value :msk:const:`onoffkey.on`.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_BI_IGNORE_NUM_ERROR
p.cmnt: If the parameter :msk:iparam:`intpnt_basis` has the value :msk:const:`basindtype.no_error` and the interior-point optimizer has terminated due to a numerical problem, then basis identification is performed if this parameter has the value :msk:const:`onoffkey.on`.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_MAX_NUM_COR
p.cmnt: Controls the maximum number of correctors allowed by the multiple corrector procedure. A negative value means that |mosek| is making the choice.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_USE
p.cmnt: Controls whether the presolve is applied to a problem before it is optimized.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_LEVEL
p.cmnt: Currently not used.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_PRESOLVE
p.cmnt: Controls amount of output printed by the presolve procedure. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_LINDEP_USE
p.cmnt: Controls whether the linear constraints are checked for linear dependencies.

values_from.ref: Turns the linear dependency check on.
Turns the linear dependency check off.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_ELIMINATOR_MAX_NUM_TRIES
p.cmnt: Control the maximum number of times the eliminator is tried. A negative value implies |mosek| decides.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_ELIMINATOR_MAX_FILL
p.cmnt: Controls the maximum amount of fill-in that can be created by one pivot in the elimination phase of the presolve. A negative value means the parameter value is selected automatically.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_MAX_NUM_REDUCTIONS
p.cmnt: Controls the maximum number of reductions performed by the presolve. The value of the parameter is normally only changed in connection with debugging. A negative value implies that an infinite number of reductions are allowed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_STABILITY_PRIORITY
p.cmnt: Controls how high priority the numerical stability should be given.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_PRIMAL_CRASH
p.cmnt:
Controls whether crashing is performed in the primal simplex optimizer.
In general, if a basis consists of more than (100-this parameter value)\% fixed variables, then a crash will be performed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_SIM
p.cmnt: Controls amount of output printed by the simplex optimizer. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_SIM_MINOR
p.cmnt: Currently not in use.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_SIM_FREQ
p.cmnt: Controls how frequent the simplex optimizer outputs information about the optimization and how frequent the user-defined callback function is called.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_PRIMAL_RESTRICT_SELECTION
p.cmnt:
The primal simplex optimizer can use a so-called restricted selection/pricing strategy to chooses the outgoing variable. Hence, if restricted selection is applied, then the primal simplex optimizer first choose a subset of all the potential incoming variables. Next, for some time it will choose the incoming variable only among the subset. From time to time the subset is redefined.
A larger value of this parameter implies that the optimizer will be more aggressive in its restriction strategy, i.e. a value of 0 implies that the restriction strategy is not applied at all.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_PRIMAL_SELECTION
p.cmnt: Controls the choice of the incoming variable, known as the selection strategy, in the primal simplex optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_DUAL_RESTRICT_SELECTION
p.cmnt:
The dual simplex optimizer can use a so-called restricted selection/pricing strategy to chooses the outgoing variable. Hence, if restricted selection is applied, then the dual simplex optimizer first choose a subset of all the potential outgoing variables. Next, for some time it will choose the outgoing variable only among the subset. From time to time the subset is redefined.
A larger value of this parameter implies that the optimizer will be more aggressive in its restriction strategy, i.e. a value of 0 implies that the restriction strategy is not applied at all.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_DUAL_SELECTION
p.cmnt: Controls the choice of the incoming variable, known as the selection strategy, in the dual simplex optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_MAX_ITERATIONS
p.cmnt: Maximum number of iterations that can be used by a simplex optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_HOTSTART_LU
p.cmnt: Determines if the simplex optimizer should exploit the initial factorization.

values_from.ref: Factorization is reused if possible.
Factorization is recomputed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_REFACTOR_FREQ
p.cmnt:
Controls how frequent the basis is refactorized. The value 0 means that the optimizer determines the best point of refactorization.
It is strongly recommended NOT to change this parameter.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_MODE
p.cmnt: Controls whether the optimizer includes the integer restrictions when solving a (mixed) integer optimization problem.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_MIO
p.cmnt: Controls the log level for the mixed-integer optimizer. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_MIO_FREQ
p.cmnt: Controls how frequent the mixed-integer optimizer prints the log line. It will print line every time :msk:iparam:`log_mio_freq` relaxations have been solved.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_MAX_NUM_RELAXS
p.cmnt: Maximum number of relaxations allowed during the branch and bound search. A negative value means infinite.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_MAX_NUM_BRANCHES
p.cmnt: Maximum number of branches allowed during the branch and bound search. A negative value means infinite.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_MAX_NUM_SOLUTIONS
p.cmnt: The mixed-integer optimizer can be terminated after a certain number of different feasible solutions has been located. If this parameter has the value :math:`n>0`, then the mixed-integer optimizer will be terminated when :math:`n` feasible solutions have been located.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_NODE_SELECTION
p.cmnt: Controls the node selection strategy employed by the mixed-integer optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_HEURISTIC_LEVEL
p.cmnt: Controls the heuristic employed by the mixed-integer optimizer to locate an initial good integer feasible solution. A value of zero means the heuristic is not used at all. A larger value than :math:`0` means that a gradually more sophisticated heuristic is used which is computationally more expensive. A negative value implies that the optimizer chooses the heuristic. Normally a value around :math:`3` to :math:`5` should be optimal.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_PROBING_LEVEL
p.cmnt:
Controls the amount of probing employed by the mixed-integer optimizer in presolve.
-1. The optimizer chooses the level of probing employed
0. Probing is disabled
1. A low amount of probing is employed
2. A medium amount of probing is employed
3. A high amount of probing is employed

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CUT_SELECTION_LEVEL
p.cmnt:
Controls how aggressively generated cuts are selected to be included in the relaxation.
-1. The optimizer chooses the level of cut selection
0. Generated cuts less likely to be added to the relaxation
1. Cuts are more aggressively selected to be included in the relaxation

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_VB_DETECTION_LEVEL
p.cmnt:
Controls how much effort is put into detecting variable bounds.
-1. The optimizer chooses
0. No variable bounds are detected
1. Only detect variable bounds that are directly represented in the problem
2. Detect variable bounds in probing

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_BRANCH_DIR
p.cmnt: Controls whether the mixed-integer optimizer is branching up or down by default.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_ROOT_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: Controls which optimizer is employed at the root node in the mixed-integer optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_NODE_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: Controls which optimizer is employed at the non-root nodes in the mixed-integer optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_PERSPECTIVE_REFORMULATE
p.cmnt: Enables or disables perspective reformulation in presolve.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_DATA_FORMAT
p.cmnt: Format of the data file to be read.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_DATA_COMPRESSED
p.cmnt: If this option is turned on,it is assumed that the data file is compressed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_KEEP_FREE_CON
p.cmnt: Controls whether the free constraints are included in the problem.

values_from.ref: The free constraints are kept.
The free constraints are discarded.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_MPS_FORMAT
p.cmnt: Controls how strictly the MPS file reader interprets the MPS format.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_MPS_FORMAT
p.cmnt: Controls in which format the MPS is written.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_MPS_WIDTH
p.cmnt: Controls the maximal number of characters allowed in one line of the MPS file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_DEBUG
p.cmnt: Turns on additional debugging information when reading files.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_LP_QUOTED_NAMES
p.cmnt: If a name is in quotes when reading an LP file, the quotes will be removed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_DATA_FORMAT
p.cmnt:
.. msk_only:: not optimizer
Controls the file format when writing task data to a file.
.. msk_only:: optimizer
Controls the data format when a task is written using :msk:func:`task.writedata`.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_DATA_PARAM
p.cmnt: If this option is turned on the parameter settings are written to the data file as parameters.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_FREE_CON
p.cmnt: Controls whether the free constraints are written to the data file.

values_from.ref: The free constraints are written.
The free constraints are discarded.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_GENERIC_NAMES
p.cmnt: Controls whether the generic names or user-defined names are used in the data file.

values_from.ref: Generic names are used.
Generic names are not used.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_GENERIC_NAMES_IO
p.cmnt: Index origin used in generic names.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_DATA_COMPRESSED
p.cmnt: Controls whether the data file is compressed while it is written. 0 means no compression while higher values mean more compression.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_MPS_INT
p.cmnt: Controls if marker records are written to the MPS file to indicate whether variables are integer restricted.

values_from.ref: Marker records are written.
Marker records are not written.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_LP_STRICT_FORMAT
p.cmnt: Controls whether LP output files satisfy the LP format strictly.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_LP_QUOTED_NAMES
p.cmnt: If this option is turned on, then |mosek| will quote invalid LP names when writing an LP file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_LP_LINE_WIDTH
p.cmnt: Maximum width of line in an LP file written by |mosek|.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_LP_TERMS_PER_LINE
p.cmnt: Maximum number of terms on a single line in an LP file written by |mosek|. 0 means unlimited.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_LP_FULL_OBJ
p.cmnt: Write all variables, including the ones with 0-coefficients, in the objective.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_PRECISION
p.cmnt: Controls the precision with which ``double`` numbers are printed in the MPS data file. In general it is not worthwhile to use a value higher than 15.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_SOL_IGNORE_INVALID_NAMES
p.cmnt: Even if the names are invalid MPS names, then they are employed when writing the solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_SOL_HEAD
p.cmnt: Controls whether the header section is written to the solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_SOL_CONSTRAINTS
p.cmnt: Controls whether the constraint section is written to the solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_SOL_VARIABLES
p.cmnt: Controls whether the variables section is written to the solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_SOL_BARVARIABLES
p.cmnt: Controls whether the symmetric matrix variables section is written to the solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_BAS_HEAD
p.cmnt: Controls whether the header section is written to the basic solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_BAS_CONSTRAINTS
p.cmnt: Controls whether the constraint section is written to the basic solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_BAS_VARIABLES
p.cmnt: Controls whether the variables section is written to the basic solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_INT_HEAD
p.cmnt: Controls whether the header section is written to the integer solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_INT_CONSTRAINTS
p.cmnt: Controls whether the constraint section is written to the integer solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_INT_VARIABLES
p.cmnt: Controls whether the variables section is written to the integer solution file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SOL_READ_NAME_WIDTH
p.cmnt: When a solution is read by |mosek| and some constraint, variable or cone names contain blanks, then a maximum name width much be specified. A negative value implies that no name contain blanks.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SOL_READ_WIDTH
p.cmnt: Controls the maximal acceptable width of line in the solutions when read by |mosek|.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INFEAS_REPORT_AUTO
p.cmnt: Controls whether an infeasibility report is automatically produced after the optimization if the problem is primal or dual infeasible.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INFEAS_REPORT_LEVEL
p.cmnt: Controls the amount of information presented in an infeasibility report. Higher values imply more information.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INFEAS_GENERIC_NAMES
p.cmnt: Controls whether generic names are used when an infeasible subproblem is created.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_INFEAS_ANA
p.cmnt: Controls amount of output printed by the infeasibility analyzer procedures. A higher level implies that more information is logged.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LICENSE_WAIT
p.cmnt: If all licenses are in use |mosek| returns with an error code. However, by turning on this parameter |mosek| will wait for an available license.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LICENSE_SUPPRESS_EXPIRE_WRNS
p.cmnt: Controls whether license features expire warnings are suppressed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LICENSE_PAUSE_TIME
p.cmnt: If :msk:iparam:`license_wait`\ = :msk:const:`onoffkey.on` and no license is available, then |mosek| sleeps a number of milliseconds between each check of whether a license has become free.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LICENSE_DEBUG
p.cmnt: This option is used to turn on debugging of the license manager.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SOL_FILTER_KEEP_BASIC
p.cmnt: If turned on, then basic and super basic constraints and variables are written to the solution file independent of the filter setting.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SOL_FILTER_KEEP_RANGED
p.cmnt: If turned on, then ranged constraints and variables are written to the solution file independent of the filter setting.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG
p.cmnt:
Controls the amount of log information. The value 0 implies that all log information is suppressed. A higher level implies that more information is logged.
Please note that if a task is employed to solve a sequence of optimization problems the value of this parameter is reduced by the value of :msk:iparam:`log_cut_second_opt` for the second and any subsequent optimizations.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_EXPAND
p.cmnt: Controls the amount of logging when a data item such as the maximum number constrains is expanded.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_FILE
p.cmnt: If turned on, then some log info is printed when a file is written or read.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_ORDER
p.cmnt: If turned on, then factor lines are added to the log.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_SENSITIVITY
p.cmnt:
Controls the amount of logging during the sensitivity analysis.
0. Means no logging information is produced. 1. Timing information is printed. 2. Sensitivity results are printed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_SENSITIVITY_OPT
p.cmnt: Controls the amount of logging from the optimizers employed during the sensitivity analysis. 0 means no logging information is produced.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_TASK_IGNORE_PARAM
p.cmnt: Controls whether |mosek| should ignore the parameter setting defined in the task file and use the default parameter setting instead.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_TASK_INC_SOL
p.cmnt: Controls whether the solutions are stored in the task file too.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PARAM_READ_CASE_NAME
p.cmnt: If turned on, then names in the parameter file are case sensitive.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PARAM_READ_IGN_ERROR
p.cmnt: If turned on, then errors in parameter settings is ignored.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SOLUTION_CALLBACK
p.cmnt: Indicates whether solution callbacks will be performed during the optimization.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_SCALING
p.cmnt: Controls how much effort is used in scaling the problem before a simplex optimizer is used.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_SCALING_METHOD
p.cmnt: Controls how the problem is scaled before a simplex optimizer is used.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_PRIMAL_PHASEONE_METHOD
p.cmnt: An experimental feature.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_DUAL_PHASEONE_METHOD
p.cmnt: An experimental feature.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_MAX_NUM_SETBACKS
p.cmnt: Controls how many set-backs are allowed within a simplex optimizer. A set-back is an event where the optimizer moves in the wrong direction. This is impossible in theory but may happen due to numerical problems.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_HOTSTART
p.cmnt: Controls the type of hot-start that the simplex optimizer perform.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_BASIS_FACTOR_USE
p.cmnt: Controls whether an LU factorization of the basis is used in a hot-start. Forcing a refactorization sometimes improves the stability of the simplex optimizers, but in most cases there is a performance penalty.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_DEGEN
p.cmnt: Controls how aggressively degeneration is handled.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_REFORMULATION
p.cmnt: Controls if the simplex optimizers are allowed to reformulate the problem.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_EXPLOIT_DUPVEC
p.cmnt: Controls if the simplex optimizers are allowed to exploit duplicated columns.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_SAVE_LU
p.cmnt: Controls if the LU factorization stored should be replaced with the LU factorization corresponding to the initial basis.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_NON_SINGULAR
p.cmnt: Controls if the simplex optimizer ensures a non-singular basis, if possible.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_DUAL_CRASH
p.cmnt:
Controls whether crashing is performed in the dual simplex optimizer.
If this parameter is set to :math:`x`, then a crash will be performed if a basis consists of more than :math:`(100-x)\mod f_v` entries, where :math:`f_v` is the number of fixed variables.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_STORAGE
p.cmnt: When turned on, |mosek| prints messages regarding the storage usage and allocation.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INFEAS_PREFER_PRIMAL
p.cmnt: If both certificates of primal and dual infeasibility are supplied then only the primal is used when this option is turned on.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_READ_LP_DROP_NEW_VARS_IN_BOU
p.cmnt: If this option is turned on, |mosek| will drop variables that are defined for the first time in the bounds section.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_MAX_TERMS_PER_LINE
p.cmnt: The maximum number of terms (linear and quadratic) per line when an OPF file is written.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_HINTS
p.cmnt: Write a hint section with problem dimensions in the beginning of an OPF file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_PARAMETERS
p.cmnt: Write a parameter section in an OPF file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_PROBLEM
p.cmnt: Write objective, constraints, bounds etc. to an OPF file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_HEADER
p.cmnt: Write a text header with date and |mosek| version in an OPF file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_SOLUTIONS
p.cmnt: Enable inclusion of solutions in the OPF files.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_SOL_BAS
p.cmnt: If :msk:iparam:`opf_write_solutions` is :msk:const:`onoffkey.on` and a basic solution is defined, include the basic solution in OPF files.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_SOL_ITG
p.cmnt: If :msk:iparam:`opf_write_solutions` is :msk:const:`onoffkey.on` and an integer solution is defined, write the integer solution in OPF files.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_OPF_WRITE_SOL_ITR
p.cmnt: If :msk:iparam:`opf_write_solutions` is :msk:const:`onoffkey.on` and an interior solution is defined, write the interior solution in OPF files.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRIMAL_REPAIR_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: Controls which optimizer that is used to find the optimal repair.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_ROOT_REPEAT_PRESOLVE_LEVEL
p.cmnt:
Controls whether presolve can be repeated at root node.
* -1 The optimizer chooses whether presolve is repeated * 0 Never repeat presolve * 1 Always repeat presolve

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CUT_CMIR
p.cmnt: Controls whether mixed integer rounding cuts should be generated.

values_from.ref: Turns generation of this cut class on.
Turns generation of this cut class off.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CUT_CLIQUE
p.cmnt: Controls whether clique cuts should be generated.

values_from.ref: Turns generation of this cut class on.
Turns generation of this cut class off.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CUT_IMPLIED_BOUND
p.cmnt: Controls whether implied bound cuts should be generated.

values_from.ref: Turns generation of this cut class on.
Turns generation of this cut class off.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CUT_KNAPSACK_COVER
p.cmnt: Controls whether knapsack cover cuts should be generated.

values_from.ref: Turns generation of this cut class on.
Turns generation of this cut class off.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CUT_GMI
p.cmnt: Controls whether GMI cuts should be generated.

values_from.ref: Turns generation of this cut class on.
Turns generation of this cut class off.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SENSITIVITY_TYPE
p.cmnt: Controls which type of sensitivity analysis is to be performed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_CONSTRUCT_SOL
p.cmnt: If set to :msk:const:`onoffkey.on` and all integer variables have been given a value for which a feasible mixed integer solution exists, then |mosek| generates an initial solution to the mixed integer problem by fixing all integer values and solving the remaining problem.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_LINDEP_REL_WORK_TRH
p.cmnt: The linear dependency check is potentially computationally expensive.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_PRESOLVE_LINDEP_ABS_WORK_TRH
p.cmnt: The linear dependency check is potentially computationally expensive.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SENSITIVITY_ALL
p.cmnt:
.. msk_only:: not optimizer
Not applicable.
.. msk_only:: optimizer
If set to :msk:const:`onoffkey.on`, then :msk:func:`task.sensitivityreport` analyzes all bounds and variables instead of reading a specification from the file.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_FEAS_REPAIR
p.cmnt: Controls the amount of output printed when performing feasibility repair. A value higher than one means extensive logging.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_CACHE_LICENSE
p.cmnt:
Specifies if the license is kept checked out for the lifetime of the mosek environment (:msk:const:`onoffkey.on`) or returned to the server immediately after the optimization (:msk:const:`onoffkey.off`).
.. msk_only:: optimizer
By default the license is checked out for the lifetime of the |mosek| environment by the first call to :msk:func:`task.optimize`.
.. msk_only:: not optimizer
By default the license is checked out for the lifetime of the |mosek| environment by the first call to the optimizer.
Check-in and check-out of licenses have an overhead. Frequent communication with the license server should be avoided.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_INTPNT_REGULARIZATION_USE
p.cmnt: Controls whether regularization is allowed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_SOLVE_FORM
p.cmnt: Controls whether the primal or the dual problem is solved by the primal-/dual-simplex optimizer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SIM_SWITCH_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: The simplex optimizer sometimes chooses to solve the dual problem instead of the primal problem. This implies that if you have chosen to use the dual simplex optimizer and the problem is dualized, then it actually makes sense to use the primal simplex optimizer instead. If this parameter is on and the problem is dualized and furthermore the simplex optimizer is chosen to be the primal (dual) one, then it is switched to the dual (primal).

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_IGNORE_INCOMPATIBLE_ITEMS
p.cmnt: Controls if the writer ignores incompatible problem items when writing files.

values_from.ref: Ignore items that cannot be written to the current output file format.
Produce an error if the problem contains items that cannot the written to the current output file format.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_CHECK_CONVEXITY
p.cmnt: Specify the level of convexity check on quadratic problems.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_LOG_CHECK_CONVEXITY
p.cmnt: Controls logging in convexity check on quadratic problems. Set to a positive value to turn logging on. If a quadratic coefficient matrix is found to violate the requirement of PSD (NSD) then a list of negative (positive) pivot elements is printed. The absolute value of the pivot elements is also shown.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_AUTO_SORT_A_BEFORE_OPT
p.cmnt: Controls whether the elements in each column of :math:`A` are sorted before an optimization is performed. This is not required but makes the optimization more deterministic.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_SENSITIVITY_OPTIMIZER
p.cmnt: Controls which optimizer is used for optimal partition sensitivity analysis.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_WRITE_XML_MODE
p.cmnt: Controls if linear coefficients should be written by row or column when writing in the XML file format.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_ANA_SOL_BASIS
p.cmnt: Controls whether the basis matrix is analyzed in solution analyzer.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_ANA_SOL_PRINT_VIOLATED
p.cmnt:
.. msk_only:: optimizer
Controls whether a list of violated constraints is printed when calling :msk:func:`task.analyzesolution`.
.. msk_only:: not optimizer
Controls whether a list of violated constraints is printed.
All constraints violated by more than the value set by the parameter :msk:dparam:`ana_sol_infeas_tol` will be printed.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_BASIS_SOLVE_USE_PLUS_ONE
p.cmnt:
If a slack variable is in the basis, then the corresponding column in the basis is a unit vector with -1 in the right position. However, if this parameter is set to :msk:const:`onoffkey.on`, -1 is replaced by 1.
.. msk_only:: optimizer
This has significance for the results returned by the :msk:func:`task.solvewithbasis` function.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_COMPRESS_STATFILE
p.cmnt: Control compression of stat files.

p.name: MSK_IPAR_MIO_RINS_MAX_NODES
p.cmnt: Controls the maximum number of nodes allowed in each call to the RINS heuristic. The default value of -1 means that the value is determined automatically. A value of zero turns off the heuristic.

c.name: MSK_SOL_STA_NEAR_DUAL_FEAS

c.name: MSK_SOL_STA_NEAR_PRIM_AND_DUAL_FEAS

c.name: MSK_SOL_STA_DUAL_ILLPOSED_CER

c.name: MSK_SOL_STA_INTEGER_OPTIMAL

c.name: MSK_OBJECTIVE_SENSE_MAXIMIZE

c.name: MSK_BK_UP
c.cmnt: The constraint or variable has an infinite lower bound and an finite upper bound.

c.name: MSK_BK_FX
c.cmnt: The constraint or variable is fixed.

c.name: MSK_BK_FR
c.cmnt: The constraint or variable is free.

c.name: MSK_BK_RA
c.cmnt: The constraint or variable is ranged.

c.name: MSK_BI_NEVER
c.cmnt: Never do basis identification.

c.name: MSK_BI_ALWAYS
c.cmnt: Basis identification is always performed even if the interior-point optimizer terminates abnormally.

c.name: MSK_BI_NO_ERROR
c.cmnt: Basis identification is performed if the interior-point optimizer terminates without an error.

c.name: MSK_BI_IF_FEASIBLE
c.cmnt: Basis identification is not performed if the interior-point optimizer terminates with a problem status saying that the problem is primal or dual infeasible.

c.name: MSK_BI_RESERVERED
c.cmnt: Not currently in use.

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_FREE
c.cmnt: The mixed-integer optimizer decides which branch to choose.

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_UP
c.cmnt: The mixed-integer optimizer always chooses the up branch first.

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_DOWN

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_NEAR

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_FAR

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_ROOT_LP
c.cmnt: Chose direction based on root lp value of selected variable.

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_GUIDED
c.cmnt: Branch in direction of current incumbent.

c.name: MSK_BRANCH_DIR_PSEUDOCOST
c.cmnt: Branch based on the pseudocost of the variable.

c.name: MSK_LIINF_MIO_PRESOLVED_ANZ

c.name: MSK_LIINF_MIO_INTPNT_ITER

c.name: MSK_LIINF_BI_DUAL_ITER
c.cmnt: Number of dual pivots performed in the basis identification.

c.name: MSK_LIINF_BI_CLEAN_PRIMAL_ITER

c.name: MSK_LIINF_BI_CLEAN_DUAL_ITER

c.name: MSK_LIINF_BI_CLEAN_PRIMAL_DEG_ITER

* an interior-point solution, * an basic solution, * and an integer solution.

c.name: MSK_RES_TRM_STALL
c.cmnt:
The optimizer is terminated due to slow progress.
Stalling means that numerical problems prevent the optimizer from making reasonable progress and that it make no sense to continue. In many cases this happens if the problem is badly scaled or otherwise ill-conditioned. There is no guarantee that the solution will be (near) feasible or near optimal. However, often stalling happens near the optimum, and the returned solution may be of good quality. Therefore, it is recommended to check the status of then solution. If the solution near optimal the solution is most likely good enough for most practical purposes.
Please note that if a linear optimization problem is solved using the interior-point optimizer with basis identification turned on, the returned basic solution likely to have high accuracy, even though the optimizer stalled.
Some common causes of stalling are a) badly scaled models, b) near feasible or near infeasible problems and c) a non-convex problems. Case c) is only relevant for general non-linear problems. It is not possible in general for |mosek| to check if a specific problems is convex since such a check would be NP hard in itself. This implies that care should be taken when solving problems involving general user defined functions.

p.name: MSK_DPAR_CHECK_CONVEXITY_REL_TOL
p.cmnt:
This parameter controls when the full convexity check declares a problem to be non-convex. Increasing this tolerance relaxes the criteria for declaring the problem non-convex.
A problem is declared non-convex if negative (positive) pivot elements are detected in the Cholesky factor of a matrix which is required to be PSD (NSD). This parameter controls how much this non-negativity requirement may be violated.
If :math:`d_i` is the pivot element for column :math:`i`, then the matrix :math:`Q` is considered to not be PSD if:
.. math:: d_i \leq - |Q_{ii}| \mathtt{check\_convexity\_rel\_tol}
